The Pentagon announced Tuesday it will exhume and try to identify the remains of 429 sailors and Marines killed on the USS Oklahoma on December 7, 1941 . 
  The ship capsized after being hit by nine torpedoes during the Japanese assault on Pearl Harbor . 
  The men are currently buried as unknowns in Honolulu's National Memorial Cemetery of the Pacific . 
  The move is part of a new Pentagon policy on disinterring remains of unknown troops . 
  Altogether, 429 were killed in the attack and only 35 were identified . 
 